    "doi": "10.1521/soco.1991.9.1.67",
    "mechanism": "Combine base-rate frequency information with individuating entity-level information under Bayesian inference principles, where the weight placed on each information source is modulated by contextual appropriateness. Model assumes a listener interprets source credibility via cooperative conversational norms (relevance, truthfulness, informativeness). When individuating information is attributed to an authoritative source and base-rate information is implicit or unstated, the learner assigns higher likelihood to the source providing explicit individuating data. The posterior probability of an entity belonging to a category is reweighted according to the relative informativeness and conversational relevance of the two information types.",
