    "doi": "10.1037/0278-7393.10.4.680",
    "mechanism": "Decompose repetition priming effects into two separable components via episodic and lexical memory systems: (1) a frequency-independent lexical effect occurring within milliseconds, insensitive to word frequency class; (2) a longer-term episodic effect proportional to trace strength of the prime encoding, modulated by word frequency. Model assumes the frequency attenuation of observed priming (stronger effect for low-frequency words) arises from the episodic component overwhelming the stable lexical component for low-frequency items. Test by comparing priming under conditions where the prime is masked (eliminating episodic traces) versus unmasked.",
