    "doi": "10.1037/h0031564",
    "mechanism": "Model pair-wise word recognition decisions as two successive dependent binary classifications: evaluate whether each string is a word. Assume latent dependence between the two decisions such that confirming one string is a word influences the likelihood of confirming the second string is a word. Model retrieval time as decreasing with associative strength between the two entities, and as exhibiting directional asymmetries (response time to first string status affects processing of second string status). Estimate decision latency as a function of association strength and word/nonword status combinations.",
